metadata.name: Isola della Scala #2
metadata.description:
All things pass, all things flow,
Movement, connection, separation, all in tow.
A misstep and we're knocked off course,
But in the end, we rise, as if by force.
Like a dance of dominoes, we fall and we stand,
In this ever-changing world, we're a part of the grand.

The name of this work is the name of the city where my roots began, where the path of everything changed and new directions in life were taken.

Made with p5.js, p5.grain and much love

metadata.name: Flossom #276
metadata.description: This work is a research of flow fields, exploring generative art forms and colors. It uses various drawing methods, randomized color palettes, and layers of patterns to add multiple dimensions of variety to the work. Willing to create a visual blossom.

metadata.name: Tangentum #108
metadata.description:
We live in a multiverse: an infinite-dimensional space of variants. Everything exists here. Everything is possible. Each subset of a multiverse has its own unique laws of physics, a set of rules, and its own distinct features.

Tangentum creates a projection of a random multiverse subset to a 2-dimensional plane. Each variation is a unique representation of the force field, that exists somewhere at some point in time.

This work starts a series of my visual exploration of functions, continuity, and boundedness, and I would love to share it with you.


Please use fullscreen or download artwork in high resolution for a better viewing experience.

Tested with Chrome 107, Safari, and Firefox. Chrome is recommended, other browsers are slower on this artwork.

This creation takes Penghu, Taiwan, my hometown as the theme, and uses the style of expired films to reconstruct the scene in my memory.

metadata.name: sauce #30
metadata.description:
sauce is the sister project of "sphaghetti al dente". both have been explorations into noise, and also a look into the amount of visual complexity that can be achieved via simple math and simple shapes layered on each other...

sauce is only available for the holders of "spaghetti al dente", and the reason I go out of my way to make it a free mint as usual is that this project will give 99% of both the primary and the secondary proceeds to IRAN. let's help as much as any of us can...

I have imported the wallet list of holders of spaghetti but removed the address-only wallets , my apologies if your wallet got chopped, but anyway the edition number is already way way lower than spaghetti.

Sauce also completes my self-imposed task/burden of publishing 12 projects in my first year in genart. I have started exactly on 3rd of january last year to learn and thanks to all of your generosity and interest in my work, I was able to finish my mission. 

peace.

objkt.name: Ode to Bugs and Happy Accidents #119

metadata.name: Ode to Bugs and Happy Accidents #119
metadata.description:
“If debugging is the process of removing software bugs, then programming must be the process of putting them in.”

― Edsger W. Dijkstra


This artwork is dedicated to happy accidents, mistakes, and bugs. Every key part of it is based on some sort of failure: wrong variable value, unstopped recursion, untimely function call. And sometimes it leads to pleasant results.

It was created to celebrate #fxhashturnsone event.

The earnings are partly donated to:
- Processing Foundation
- #TezosStandsWithUkraine
